summary: Jhogo sucked in his breath. “Khaleesi, no.” The bell in his braid rang softly as he dismounted. “You must not get any closer. Do...
body:
Jhogo sucked in his breath. “Khaleesi, no.” The bell in his braid rang softly as he dismounted. “You must not get any closer. Do not let them touch you! Do not!”                  

Dany walked right past him. There was an old man on the ground a few feet away, moaning and staring up at the grey belly of the clouds. She knelt beside him, wrinkling her nose at the smell, and pushed back his dirty grey hair to feel his brow. “His flesh is on fire. I need water to bathe him.”

summary: I've seen theories that Randyll Tarly is going to defect to Team fAegon. When you add the Golden Company, that's most of...
question: I've seen theories that Randyll Tarly is going to defect to Team fAegon. When you add the Golden Company, that's most of show!Cersei's conventional military assets. Do you think that sequence of final battles will feature the survivors of the battle for the Dawn turning on King Aegon, after he refused to help?  Like a Scouring of the Shire thing? Maybe he'll have Cersei locked up like Queen Alicent, and Jaime will rescue her, only to choke her out when she tries to set off the basement wildfire?
answer: Nope. I think the problems Aegon presents are too immediate for Dany to sail north around, and the internal reasoning for her going north at this point very thin. As of ADWD, Aegon’s making real, solid steps to take the stuff that Dany wants. Dany’s got to deal with him first, before dealing with narrative endgame things.

summary: I just started watching Game of Thrones. I've followed a few specific characters over the years but never really watched the...
question: I just started watching Game of Thrones. I've followed a few specific characters over the years but never really watched the show. When I found out what they did to Daenerys I was so pissed! I decided to start watching it out of morbid curiosity. Let me tell you, I have even more of a negative attitude about it now. I've literally watched a man sacrifice babies, entire families slaughtered, people tortured and raped, but DaNy Is ThE vIlLaIn AnD nEeDs To DiE *rolls eyes* seriously, fuck d&d
answer:
It’s even worse if you’ve read the books. Show!Dany is pretty set on the Throne, even if for altruistic reasons. Book!Dany is more unsure what her purpose is. She had begun to think it was to be a wife and mother, and she was happy with that. But once her husband and son die and she’s got dragons, she has a huge target on her back.

She’s just turned 14, and is alone in a desert with the few people that stuck by her. I’m not sure why they chose to have her kill Doreah in the show, because in the books she died in the Red Waste of a wasting disease. But once she figures out Qarth isn’t safe either she’s got three options: be murdered for her dragons, be murdered because she’s a Targaryen, or amass enough power that she’s got a reasonable amount of protection.

In her POV chapters, we see her thinking about the brief childhood home she had, and how she would run away with Daario if he asked. We see her tending to the sick despite the protests of her advisers, and trying to adopt some of the customs of the cities she is in to fit in better.

That’s one of the things that really bugs me about GoT. While many characters have negative traits taken away, Dany has more positive traits taken away. They want her to represent the sterotypical post-rebellion version of what a Targaryen should be in the eyes of Robert and his allies. They do this with Jon too, aligning him with all of the sterotypical Stark characteristics and ignoring his less savory traits.
